---Using github------------------------------------------

so if you screwed up you just        rm -rf .git          and it removes all the git stuff

git init 
git add .
git commit -m "message"

gh repo create 
git remote add origin https://github.com/anyamao/repo.name
git push -u origin master

when want to update to the latst version - git pull origin master

when prompted for a password

ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"

eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519

cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub - copy the key

add the key to github settings ssh keys new ssh key

ssh -T git@github.com    


turns out you need to copy with ssh and then it will be ok

so just git remote add-url origin git@github.com:username/repo.git

